geneVariantDescriptions.description: ALK L1196M lies within the protein kinase domain of the Alk protein (UniProt.org). L1196M is predicted to confer a gain of function to the Alk protein as demonstrated by transformation activity and modest autophosphorylation of Alk in culture (PMID: 25517749), and confers resistance to Alk inhibitors in the context of ALK rearrangements in culture and in vivo (PMID: 21613408, PMID: 25421750, PMID: 31452835).
